agram: is old school still the best? <em>Clin Imaging</em> 2018;51:23–29.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.clinimag.2018.01.010">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29414520/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Diagnosing+conduit+leak+after+esophagectomy+for+esophageal+cancer+by+computed+tomography+leak+protocol+and+standard+esophagram%3A+is+old+school+still+the+best%3F&amp;author=D+Palacio&amp;author=EM+Marom&amp;author=A+Correa&amp;author=SL+Betancourt-Cuellar&amp;author=WL+Hofstetter&amp;publication_year=2018&amp;journal=Clin+Imaging&amp;pages=23-29&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.clinimag.2018.01.010&amp;pmid=29414520">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">21.</div><div id="r21" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Pannu D, Yang D, Abbitt PL, Draganov PV. Prospective evaluation of CT esophagram findings after peroral endoscopic myotomy. <em>Gastrointest Endosc</em> 2016;84(3):408–415.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.gie.2016.02.022">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26907745/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Prospective+evaluation+of+CT+esophagram+findings+after+peroral+endoscopic+myotomy&amp;author=D+Pannu&amp;author=D+Yang&amp;author=PL+Abbitt&amp;author=PV+Draganov&amp;publication_year=2016&amp;journal=Gastrointest+Endosc&amp;pages=408-415&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.gie.2016.02.022&amp;pmid=26907745">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">22.</div><div id="r22" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citati